ng>EA vs. e/acc</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">One of the biggest debates i=
n my corner of Twitter, which burst out into the world with this month&#821=
7;s OpenAI drama, is Effective Altruism (EA) vs. Effective Accelerationism =
(e/acc).&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s the latest manifestation of =
an age-old struggle between those who believe we should grow, and those who=
 don&#8217;t, and the perfect case study through which to explore the narra=
tive tug-of-war.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If you look at either side in i=
solation, both views seem extreme.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, =
64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">EA (which I&#=
8217;m using as a shorthand for the AI-risk team), believes that there is a=
 very good chance that AI is going to kill all of us. Given the fact that t=
here will be trillions of humans in the coming millennia, even if there&#82=
17;s a 1% chance AI will kill us all, preventing that from happening will s=
ave tens or hundreds of billions of expected lives. We need to stop AI deve=
lopment before we get to AGI, whatever the cost.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color=
: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"=
><span>As that team&#8217;s captain, Eliezer Yudkowsky, </span><a href=3D"h=
ttps://substack.com/redirect/3cff496a-c27e-4b62-b288-433fca74ac1d?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">wrote in </a><em><a href=
=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/3cff496a-c27e-4b62-b288-433fca74ac1d?j=3D=
eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Time</a><span>:</s=
pan></em></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 2=
0px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>Shut down all =
the large GPU clusters (the large computer farms where the most powerful AI=
s are refined). Shut down all the large training runs. Put a ceiling on how=
 much computing power anyone is allowed to use in training an AI system, an=
d move it downward over the coming years to compensate for more efficient t=
raining algorithms. No exceptions for governments and militaries. Make imme=
diate multinational agreements to prevent the prohibited activities from mo=
ving elsewhere. Track all GPUs sold. If intelligence says that a country ou=
tside the agreement is building a GPU cluster, be less scared of a shooting=
 conflict between nations than of the moratorium being violated; be willing=
 to destroy a rogue datacenter by airstrike.</em></p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>The idea that we should bomb datacenters to prevent the dev=
elopment of AI, </span><em>taken in a vacuum</em><span>, is absurd, as many=
 of AI&#8217;s supporters were quick to point out.&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">e/acc (which I&#8217;m using as a shorthand for the pro-AI team) =
believes that AI won&#8217;t kill us all and that we should do whatever we =
can to accelerate it. They believe that technology is good, capitalism is g=
ood, and that the combination of the two, the techno-capital machine, is th=
e &#8220;engine of perpetual material creation, growth, and abundance. We n=
eed to protect the techno-capital machine at all costs.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><span>Marc Andreessen, who rocks &#8220;e/acc&#8221; in his </spa=
n><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/71371869-ee70-4f44-8e99-3b4eb331=
4b3f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" re=
l style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">twitter bio=
</a><span>, recently wrote </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redir=
ect/4915fae1-411b-43b3-b21c-ba423d37b3a0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_=
ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text=
-decoration: underline;">The Techno-Optimist Manifesto</a></em><span>, in w=
hich he makes the case for essentially unchecked technological progress. On=
e section in particular drew the ire of AI&#8217;s opponents:&#160;</span><=
/p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px 0; pad=
ding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>We have enemies.</em></p=
><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>Our enemies are not bad people &#=
8211; but rather bad ideas.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><e=
m>Our present society has been subjected to a mass demoralization campaign =
for six decades &#8211; against technology and against life &#8211; under v=
arying names like &#8220;existential risk&#8221;, &#8220;sustainability&#82=
21;, &#8220;ESG&#8221;, &#8220;Sustainable Development Goals&#8221;, &#8220=
;social responsibility&#8221;, &#8220;stakeholder capitalism&#8221;, &#8220=
;Precautionary Principle&#8221;, &#8220;trust and safety&#8221;, &#8220;tec=
h ethics&#8221;, &#8220;risk management&#8221;, &#8220;de-growth&#8221;, &#=
8220;the limits of growth&#8221;.</em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20p=
x;"><em>This demoralization campaign is based on bad ideas of the past &#82=
11; zombie ideas, many derived from Communism, disastrous then and now &#82=
11; that have refused to die.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>=
The idea that things most people view as good &#8211; like sustainability, =
ethics, and risk management &#8211; </span><em>taken in a vacuum</em><span>=
, seems absurd, as many journalists and bloggers were quick to point out.&#=
160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">What critics of both pieces either missed =
is that neither argument should be taken in a vacuum. Nuance isn&#8217;t th=
e point of any one specific argument. You pull the edges hard so that nuanc=
e can emerge in the middle.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>While there ar=
e people on both teams who support their side&#8217;s most radical views &#=
8211; a complete AI shutdown on one side, unchecked techno-capital growth o=
n the other &#8211; what&#8217;s really happening is a game of narrative tu=
g-of-war in which </span><strong>the knot is regulation</strong><span>.&#16=
0;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-heig=
ht: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>EA would like to see AI regulated, and=
 </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/a169403b-4e1d-4616-bb71-61=
ca9a0d6f50?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">would=
 like to be the ones who write the regulation</a><span>. e/acc would like t=
o see AI remain open and not controlled by any one group, be it a governmen=
t or a company.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>One side tugs by wa=
rning that AI Will Kill Us All in order to scare the public and the governm=
ent into hasty regulation, the other side tugs back by arguing that </span>=
<a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/47337de5-5eab-4209-8c17-d8be8ceaf2=
a4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel =
style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">AI Will Save =
the World</a><span> to stave off regulation for long enough that people can=
 experience its benefits firsthand.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(=
64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Perso=
nally, and unsurprisingly, I&#8217;m on the side of the techno-optimists. T=
hat doesn&#8217;t mean that I believe that technology is a panacea, or that=
 there aren&#8217;t real concerns that need to be addressed.&#160;</p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">It means that I believe that growth is better than stagnation,=
 that problems have solutions, that history shows that both technological p=
rogress and capitalism have improved humans&#8217; standard of living, and =
that bad regulation is a bigger risk than no regulation.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">While the world shifts based on narrative tug-of-wars, there is a=
lso truth, or at least fact patterns. Doomers &#8211; from Malthus to Ehrli=
ch &#8211; continue to be proven wrong, but fear sells, and as a result, th=
e mainstream narrative continues to lean anti-tech. The fear is that restri=
ctive regulation is put in place before the truth can emerge.&#160;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;">Because the thing about this game of narrative tug-of-war is =
that it&#8217;s not a fair one.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The anti-g=
rowth side needs only to pull hard and long enough to get regulation enacte=
d. Once it&#8217;s in place, it&#8217;s hard to overturn; typically, it rat=
chets up. </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/37491369-3843-485=
c-9cf4-02a8e321fa46?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underlin=
e;">Nuclear energy is a clear example</a><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><strong>If they can pull the knot over the regulation line, they =
win, game over.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The pro-gr=
owth side has to keep pulling for long enough for the truth to emerge in sp=
ite of all the messiness that comes with any new technology, for entreprene=
urs to build products that prove out the promise, and for creative humans t=
o devise solutions that address concerns without neutering progress.&#160;<=
/p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>They need to keep the tug-of-war going long en=
ough for solutions to emerge in the middle.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;"><span>Yesterday, Ethereum co-founder Vitalik Buterin wrote a piece cal=
led </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/28d1c12d-9bf4-4e9d-=
a01f-c31bb1c60deb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;=
">My techno-optimism</a></em><span> in which he proposed one such solution:=
 d/acc.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The &#8220;d,&#8221; he wro=
te, &#8220;can stand for many things; particularly, </span><strong>defense<=
/strong><span>, </span><strong>decentralization</strong><span>, </span><str=
ong>democracy</strong><span> and </span><strong>differential</strong><span>=
=2E&#8221; It means using technology to=
 develop AI in a way that protects aga=
inst potential pitfalls and prioritizes human flourishing.&#160;</span></p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">On one side, the AI safety movement pulls with the messag=
e: &#8220;you should just stop.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">On the ot=
her, e/acc says, &#8220;you&#8217;re already a hero just the way you are.&#=
8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-he=
ight: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Vitalik proposes d/acc as a third, middle =
way:&#160;</p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: =
20px 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>A d/acc messa=
ge, one that says &quot;you should build, and build profitable things, but =
be much more selective and intentional in making sure you are building thin=
gs that help you and humanity thrive&quot;, may be a winner.</em></p></bloc=
kquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26=
px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s a synthesis, one he argues can appeal t=
o people whatever their philosophy (as long as the philosophy isn&#8217;t &=
#8220;regulate the technology to smithereens&#8221;):&#160;</p><div class=
