or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;">Without EA and e/acc pulling on both extremes, there may not have been r=
oom in the middle for Vitalik&#8217;s d/acc. The extremes, lacking nuance t=
hemself, create the space for nuance to emerge in the middle.&#160;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;">If EA wins, and regulation halts progress or concentrates it =
into the hands of a few companies, that room no longer exists. If the goal =
is to regulate, there&#8217;s no room for a solution that doesn&#8217;t inv=
olve regulation.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16=
px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But if the goal is human flouri=
shing, there&#8217;s plenty of room for solutions. Keeping that room open i=
s the point.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Despite the fact that Vitalik=
 explicitly disagrees with pieces of e/acc, both </span><a href=3D"https://=
substack.com/redirect/521b3918-1183-4958-8ad2-ead6448693a1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Marc Andreessen</a><span> and e/=
acc&#8217;s pseudonymous co-founder </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/=
redirect/e2290ab3-b6ba-49d5-ba1a-8ab15f1820a8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T=
7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);=
 text-decoration: underline;">Beff Jezos</a><span> shared Vitalik&#8217;s p=
ost. That&#8217;s a hint that they&#8217;re less worried about </span><em>t=
heir</em><span> solution than </span><em>a good</em><span> solution.&#160;<=
/span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Whether d/acc is the answer or not, it captures=
 the point of tugging on the extremes beautifully. Only once e/acc set the =
outer boundary could a solution that involves merging humans and AI through=
 Neuralinks be viewed as a sensible, moderate take. Ray Kurzweil made that =
point a couple decades ago and has the arrows to prove it.&#160;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;">In this and other narrative tug-of-wars, the extremes serve a pu=
rpose, but they are not the purpose. For every EA, there is an equal and op=
posite e/acc. As long as the game continues, solutions can emerge from that=
 tension.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Don&#8217;t focus on the tuggers, focu=
s on the knot.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;"><hr st=
yle=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: none; height: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padd=
